Task:

Attach Network Interface Card (NIC) to Azure Virtual Machine

The datacenter DevOps team is migrating services to Azure. They are breaking down tasks to ensure better control and optimization. You are tasked with attaching an existing network interface (NIC) to a virtual machine (VM).

An existing VM named datacenter-vm and a network interface named datacenter-nic already exist in the southcentralus region.

Attach the network interface datacenter-nic to the VM datacenter-vm.

Ensure the NIC's status is attached before submitting the task.

Make sure that the virtual machine initialization has been completed before submitting this task.

Solution:

Go to Home and type VM and then the network interfaces to see the list of VM's and network interfaces.
View that already existing nic was attached to the existing VM.
Stop the existing VM.
Once VM is stopped-->Go to Networking--> Network settings
Click attach network interface
Choose network interface - datacenter-nic to attach
Start VM, if the option is disabled - choose connect and then start VM. 
